data.meta_description: NBA Hall-of-Famer and businessman Shaquille O'Neal is trying to sell his Bell Canyon, California home for $2.5 million on Instagram instead of using a broker. Shaq bought the place in February 2018 for $1.8 million and has been trying to sell it since last December.
data.text:
NBA Hall-of-Famer and businessman Shaquille O'Neal is trying to sell his Bell Canyon, California home for $2.5 million via Instagram after buying it in February 2018 for $1.8 million.

The basketball star previously listed the home with LA-based real estate agency Compass last December but withdrew the listing and decided to try a new approach: social media.

On Thursday, O'Neal posted a video giving his 15.3 million follows a look inside his 5,217-square-foot home in a gated equestrian community outside Los Angeles (just a few miles from where Kanye and Kim Kardashian West live).

(In October, Justin Bieber posted images of the interior of his home on Instagram, writing in the caption: "I think I wanna sell my home in Beverly Hills who wants it?")

O'Neal's house has five bedrooms, four-and-a-half bathrooms and sits on a 1-acre lot, according to the post.

O'Neal has updated the property, including new carpeting, custom closets and landscaping upgrades, according to a Compass spokesperson, who previously held the listing.

"The house is walking distance from the community center, state of the art gym and tennis courts," O'Neal writes.

Take a look inside.
